         <listPerson>
            <person sex="2">
               <persName xml:id="n1" xml:lang="am">ድንቅነሽ፡ ምርጫ፡</persName>
               <persName corresp="#n1" xml:lang="am" type="normalized">Dǝnqǝnaš Mǝrč̣ā</persName>
               <persName><roleName type="title">ʾǝtege</roleName></persName>
               <occupation type="political"></occupation>
               <birth when="1833"></birth>
               <floruit>
                 Dǝnqǝnaš Mǝrč̣ā was first married to <persName ref="PRS4258GabraKi"></persName> from whom she had
                 a son, <persName ref="PRS8799seyyum"></persName>, and three daughters,
                 <persName ref="PRS1996Aradacc"></persName>, <persName ref="PRS9132Takkolac"></persName>, and
                 <persName ref="PRS2759BezuGab"></persName>. After the divorce, she married
                 <persName ref="PRS9143TaklaGi">Gobaze Gabra Madḫən</persName> in <date>1867</date>. The latter proclaimed himself
                  ʾaṣe Takla Giyorgis II in <date>1867</date>, thus Dǝnqǝnaš Mǝrč̣ā received a title of ʾǝtege. After the defeat of her
                  husband, she joined him in <placeName ref="LOC1398AmbaSa"></placeName> and stayed with him until his death. Thereafter,
                  she moved to the Imperial Court and became one of the most influential advisors of her brother
                  <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne"></persName>. After the banishment and death of her son
                  <persName ref="PRS8799seyyum"></persName>, she retreated to <placeName ref="LOC5749Sire"></placeName>.
               </floruit>
               <death when="1912"></death>
            </person>
